land was succeeded by [[Geoff York]] in July 1981.|group=note|name=\"holland\"}}\n|<ref name=\":3\" /><ref name=\":5\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{Sn|Henry|Elsworth}}\n| style=\"background-color: {{Rhodesian Front/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Rhodesian Front]] {{Small|(until 1982)}}{{refn|The Rhodesian Front was succeeded in 1981 by the [[Republican Front (Zimbabwe)|Republican Front]], and in 1984 by the [[Conservative Alliance of Zimbabwe]].|group=note|name=\"rhodesianfront\"}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Midlands (parliamentary constituency)|Midlands]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |\n| rowspan=\"2\" |<ref name=\":10\" />\n|-\n| style=\"background-color: {{Independent/meta/color}}\" |\n|Independent {{Small|(from 1982)}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{Sn|Chris|Andersen|dab=Zimbabwean politician}}\n| style=\"background-color: {{Rhodesian Front/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Rhodesian Front]] {{Small|(until 1982)}}{{refn|The Rhodesian Front was succeeded in 1981 by the [[Republican Front (Zimbabwe)|Republican Front]], and in 1984 by the [[Conservative Alliance of Zimbabwe]].|group=note|name=\"rhodesianfront\"}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Mount Pleasant (parliamentary constituency)|Mount Pleasant]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |\n| rowspan=\"2\" |<ref name=\":10\" />\n|-\n| style=\"background-color: {{Independent/meta/color}}\" |\n|Independent {{Small|(from 1982)}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{Sn|Esmond|Micklem}}\n| style=\"background-color: {{Rhodesian Front/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Rhodesian Front]] {{Small|(until 1982)}}{{refn|The Rhodesian Front was succeeded in 1981 by the [[Republican Front (Zimbabwe)|Republican Front]], and in 1984 by the [[Conservative Alliance of Zimbabwe]].|group=note|name=\"rhodesianfront\"}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Northern (parliamentary constituency)|Northern]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |\n| rowspan=\"2\" |<ref name=\":10\" />\n|-\n| style=\"background-color: {{Independent/meta/color}}\" |\n|Independent {{Small|(from 1982)}}\n|-\n|{{Sn|Ian|Smith}}\n| style=\"background-color: {{Rhodesian Front/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Rhodesian