=\"independent\"}}\n|0\n|4\n|-\n| style=\"background:{{Independent/meta/color}};\" |\n|Chiefs\n|10\n|10\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |'''Total'''\n|'''40'''\n|'''40'''\n|}\n\n=== House of Assembly ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! rowspan=\"3\" |Date\n! colspan=\"5\" |Party\n! rowspan=\"3\" |Total\n! rowspan=\"3\" |Vacant\n|-\n!\n!\n!\n!\n!\n|-\n![[Conservative Alliance of Zimbabwe|CAZ]]{{refn|The Rhodesian Front was succeeded in 1981 by the [[Republican Front (Zimbabwe)|Republican Front]], and in 1984 by the [[Conservative Alliance of Zimbabwe]].|group=note|name=\"caz\"}}\n![[United African National Council|UANC]]\n![[ZANU\u2013PF]]\n![[Zimbabwe African People's Union|ZAPU\u2013PF]]\n!{{Abbr|Ind.|Independent}}{{refn|Includes members of the [[Independent Zimbabwe Group]], a bloc formed by white independent MPs in 1983.|group=note|name=\"independent\"}}\n|-\n|14 May 1980 (opened)\n|20\n|3\n|57\n|20\n|0\n|100\n|0\n|-\n|October 1980\n|20\n|3\n|57\n|19\n|0\n|99\n|1\n|-\n|Late 1980<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3hVVAAAAYAAJ|title=Africa Research Bulletin|date=1980|publisher=Blackwell|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=5927|language=en}}</ref>\n|19\n|3\n|57\n|19\n|0\n|98\n|2\n|-\n|Early 1981<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QbkPAQAAMAAJ|title=Zimbabwe News|date=1998|publisher=Zimbabwe African National Union|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=11|language=en}}</ref>\n|19\n|3\n|57\n|20\n|0\n|99\n|1\n|-\n|January 1981<ref name=\":0\" />\n|20\n|3\n|57\n|20\n|0\n|100\n|0\n|-\n|April 1981<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/books?newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&id=Tk5EAQAAIAAJ|title=Sub-Saharan Africa Report|date=1981|publisher=Foreign Broadcast Information Service.|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=135|language=en}}</ref>\n|19\n|3\n|57\n|20\n|0\n|99\n|1\n|-\n|June 1981<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7rwtx15jZaQC|ti