vingo Province|Victoria]]\n|Convicted October 1984.{{refn|Bassopo Moyo served in Parliament until his 1984 criminal conviction.|name=\"bassopomoyo\"|group=note}}\n|<ref name=\":19\" />\n|-\n|{{Sn|Nelson|Mawema}}\n| style=\"background-color: {{ZANU-PF/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[ZANU\u2013PF]]\n|[[Masvingo Province|Victoria]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|{{Sn|Dzikamai|Mavhaire}}\n| style=\"background-color: {{ZANU-PF/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[ZANU\u2013PF]]\n|[[Masvingo Province|Victoria]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|{{Sn|Albert|Taderera}}\n| style=\"background-color: {{ZANU-PF/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[ZANU\u2013PF]]\n|[[Masvingo Province|Victoria]]\n|\n|\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" |''Source:<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.colonialrelic.com/appendixes/members-of-parliament-government-of-zimbabwe-1980/|title=Members of Parliament - Government of Zimbabwe 1980|last=Cary|first=Robert|last2=Mitchell|first2=Diana|date=1980|website=African Nationalist Leaders - Rhodesia to Zimbabwe|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>''\n|\n|}\n\n=== White seats ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n!Name\n! colspan=\"2\" |Party\n!Constituency\n!Notes\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{Sn|John|Landau}}\n| style=\"background-color: {{Rhodesian Front/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Rhodesian Front]] {{Small|(until 1982)}}{{refn|The Rhodesian Front was succeeded in 1981 by the [[Republican Front (Zimbabwe)|Republican Front]], and in 1984 by the [[Conservative Alliance of Zimbabwe]].|group=note|name=\"rhodesianfront\"}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Avondale (parliamentary constituency)|Avondale]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |\n| rowspan=\"2\" |<ref name=\":11\" />\n|-\n| style=\"background-color: {{Independent/meta/color}}\" |\n|Independent {{Small|(from 1982)}}\n|-\n|{{Sn|David Colville|Smith}}\n| style=\"background-color: {{Rhodesian Front/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Rhodesian Front]]\n|[[Borrowdale (parliamentary constituency)|Borrowdale]]\n|Resigned April 1981.{{refn|Smith was succeeded by [[John Probert]] in J